pull_requests.title: fix: tg negative id
pull_requests.body:
## Fix Telegram negative chat ID UUID conversion

### Problem
Telegram group chat IDs are often negative numbers (starting with `-`), which causes issues when converting to UUIDs with `createUniqueUuid()`. This has been causing world creation to fail because the generated IDs aren't recognized as valid UUIDs.

### Solution
Modified the code to properly handle negative Telegram chat IDs by removing the negative sign before UUID creation while still maintaining uniqueness. This ensures chat IDs like `-12345679909866` are properly converted to valid UUIDs.

### Changes
- Updated `handleNewChat` method to sanitize chat IDs before UUID creation
- Applied the same fix to the `setupEntityTracking` method
- Maintains unique identifier mapping while ensuring UUID validity

plugin-browser Package
1. AWS S3 Service Tests (10 tests)
* Coverage: AWS S3 integration for file storage
* Key tests:
    * Service initialization with proper bucket and region configuration
    * Service lifecycle management (start/stop)
    * File upload functionality with error handling
    * JSON data upload capabilities
    * Signed URL generation for secure file access
* Benefits: Ensures reliable cloud storage integration for the application
2. Video Service Tests (3 tests)
* Coverage: Video processing and management
* Key tests:
    * Service initialization and configuration
    * Video information retrieval from various sources
    * Video data processing functionality
* Benefits: Validates media handling capabilities crucial for content processing
3. Browser Service Tests (7 tests)
* Coverage: Web page interaction and content extraction
* Key tests:
    * Browser initialization and configuration
    * Page navigation and content retrieval
    * HTML processing and data extraction
    * Error handling for network issues
* Benefits: Ensures reliable web scraping and browser automation functionality
4. PDF Service Tests (9 tests)
* Coverage: PDF document processing
* Key tests:
    * PDF parsing and text extraction
    * Document structure analysis
    * Content transformation and processing
    * Error handling for malformed documents
* Benefits: Validates the system's ability to work with document-based content
5. Plugin Integration Tests (8 tests)
* Coverage: Overall plugin system integration
* Key tests:
    * Plugin registration and initialization
    * Service discovery and access
    * Configuration management
    * Inter-service communication
* Benefits: Confirms the plugin architecture works as a cohesive system
6. Type Definitions Tests (11 tests)
* Coverage: TypeScript type system validation
* Key tests:
    * Interface implementation verification
    * Type conversion and handling
    * Generic type applications
    * Type safety across module boundaries
* Benefits: Ensures type safety and provides development-time error detection
The test suite provides comprehensive validation of the plugin-browser package's core functionality, ensuring it reliably handles web content, media, document processing, and cloud storage integration.
